                                <div class="alert alert-info"> 1. BACKGROUND AND CONTEXT </div>
                                <p class="margin-top-20">KePSIE is a unique partnership between the Kenyan Government and the World Bank Group, building on long-term support for regulatory reform in the health sector through the Health in Africa program. It is the largest trial aimed at improving patient safety in low- and middle-income countries. The three main objectives and corresponding outputs are outlined below in Figure 1.  </p>
