                                </p>
                                 <br/>
                                <div class="alert alert-info"> 2. A NEW REGULATORY FRAMEWORK FOR JOINT HEALTH INSPECTIONS</div>
                                <p>
                                    A new regulatory framework was gazetted recently under Cap 242, Legal Notice No. 46 on March 21, 2016 to conduct inspections in both private and public facilities (only private facilities were inspected prior to the reform). This new regulation includes a revised Joint Health Inspection Checklist (JHIC).
A few critical elements of the new regulatory framework include:
A more detailed and standardized checklist;
A scoring system to classify facilities according to their risk levels; and
A system of warnings and sanctions for non-compliant health facilities based on their compliance category.

Table 1 shows the compliance categorization of facilities based on their scores and corresponding follow-up actions. This also implies that some facilities in your counties will face the risk of closure if they fall into the “non-compliant” category. However, based on the new regulatory framework, they will also be given opportunities to be re-inspected, creating incentives for improvement and learning.
                                </p>

